\section*{E. Primary site unknown}

If the statement, "primary site unknown", or its equivalent, appears anywhere on a certificate, code to the category for unspecified site for the morphological type involved (e.g. adenocarcinoma C80, fibrosarcoma C49.9, osteosarcoma C41.9), regardless of the site(s) mentioned elsewhere on the certificate.
